						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar in the Saṁgamēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1246.</p>						

						<p>This inscription dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1168, Parābhava, Āśvija śu. 11, Monday,</hi> records a gift of money for the offering of flowers to god <hi rend="bold">Viśvarūpadēva.</hi> The donor was <hi rend="bold">Nāgavve,</hi> the mother of <hi rend="bold">Sāteya-Nāyaka</hi> who bore the <hi rend="italic">biruda</hi> <hi rend="bold">Baḷḷeyar-Eṟeya.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of the date correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1246, September 23,</hi> which was, however <hi rend="bold">Sunday,</hi> not Monday.</p>						

						</summary>
